From: aorus-5090-egpu <noreply@example.invalid>
Date: 2026-05-08
Subject: [PATCH] AORUS Patch 0028 — attempt_count resets at post-rmInit-OK, not slot_reset_resume

Fixes a design deviation in Step 7 of Patch 0024 that left the H1
MaxAttempts gate unreachable in real-world recovery storms.

Design intent (docs/lever-m-recover-commit3-hardening-design.md § H1):
  attempt_count resets to 0 ONLY on successful recovery (slot_reset
  + verify GSP boots). NOT on probe-end alone, NOT on workqueue
  completion.

Step 7 in Patch 0024 reset attempt_count inside slot_reset_resume,
which fires after pci_reset_bus + PMC_BOOT_0 readback succeeds.
That's only HALF of "successful recovery" — slot_reset can return
RECOVERED yet rm_init_adapter still fail on the next call (e.g. WPR2
still stuck after the bus reset). In production, this is exactly the
21-attempt storm pattern observed 2026-05-06 16:14:29: each cycle
reset attempt_count 0->1->0, the gate never engaged, the storm ran.

Fix (two parts):

1. Remove atomic_set(&attempt_count, 0) from
   tb_egpu_lever_m_slot_reset_resume(). Keep success_count++ and
   TB_EGPU_GPU_STATE=READY uevent — those are still correct semantics
   for "bus reset cycle completed."

2. Add tb_egpu_lever_m_record_post_rminit_ok() helper called from
   nv.c's existing post-rmInit-OK site. Resets attempt_count to 0
   here — this is the verified-end-to-end-recovery moment. Safe
   to call on every cold-boot init (idempotent: attempt_count is
   already 0 in the no-recovery-needed case).

Behaviour after this patch:

  - Real-world storm scenario: each failed full-recovery accumulates
    attempt_count. Fire 1: bus reset OK, rm_init fails, attempt=1.
    Fire 2: attempt=2. Fire 3: attempt=3. Fire 4: attempt=4 >
    MaxAttempts=3 → surrender + PERMANENT_FAIL. Storm stops.

  - Successful end-to-end recovery: attempt_count resets at
    post-rmInit-OK so the next burst starts fresh.

  - 5-min-idle burst boundary (NVreg_TbEgpuLeverMSurrenderResetSec):
    still works as before, in the trigger function.

Discovered while preparing Phase 4 H1 MaxAttempts test: under
Patch 0024+0027 behaviour, every force_trigger fire produced a
successful slot_reset + resume cycle, attempt_count went 0->1->0,
and the gate could not be reached.

Refs: H15 hypothesis ledger entry; storm forensic
      archive/commit3-recovery-loop-2026-05-06-161429/.
---
--- a/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-lever-m-recover.h
+++ b/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-lever-m-recover.h
@@ -153,6 +153,11 @@
 pci_ers_result_t tb_egpu_lever_m_slot_reset(struct pci_dev *pdev);
 void              tb_egpu_lever_m_slot_reset_resume(struct pci_dev *pdev);
 
+/* Patch 0028 (2026-05-08): hook for nv.c's post-rmInit-OK site.
+ * Resets attempt_count to 0 — verified end-to-end recovery. Safe to
+ * call on every successful adapter init (idempotent on cold boot). */
+void tb_egpu_lever_m_record_post_rminit_ok(nv_linux_state_t *nvl);
+
 /* AORUS Mode B telemetry S1 (2026-05-08): trigger-event AER capture.
  * Reactive helper called from Q-watchdog detection and AER error_detected
  * callback. Walks GPU -> bridge -> root_port (via aorus_walk_to_root_port
--- a/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-lever-m-recover.c
+++ b/kernel-open/nvidia/nv-lever-m-recover.c
@@ -1111,8 +1111,20 @@
 /* Commit 3 (H4): pci_error_handlers resume helper.
  *
  * Called from nv_pci_resume() in nv-pci.c after slot_reset returned
- * RECOVERED. This is where we declare success: increment success_count,
- * reset attempt_count to 0, emit TB_EGPU_GPU_STATE=READY uevent.
+ * RECOVERED. This increments success_count (counting bus reset cycles
+ * that completed) and emits TB_EGPU_GPU_STATE=READY.
+ *
+ * Patch 0028 (2026-05-08): attempt_count is NO LONGER reset here.
+ * slot_reset_resume only proves the GPU is alive on the bus — but
+ * rm_init_adapter can still fail on the next call (e.g. WPR2 still
+ * stuck). Per design § H1, attempt_count must reset only on
+ * "successful recovery (slot_reset + verify GSP boots)" — slot_reset
+ * is half of that. The other half is verified at the post-rmInit-OK
+ * site in nv.c, which calls tb_egpu_lever_m_record_post_rminit_ok()
+ * below. Without this fix the H1 MaxAttempts gate is unreachable in
+ * the real-world storm scenario (the very pattern we lived through
+ * 2026-05-06): each failed full-recovery cycles attempt_count 0->1->0
+ * and the gate never engages.
  *
  * Patch 0024 v1 does NOT re-enter rm_init_adapter from this callback —
  * doing so safely requires preserving CUDA context state across reset,
@@ -1131,17 +1143,48 @@
         return;
 
     atomic_inc(&nvl->lever_m->success_count);
-    atomic_set(&nvl->lever_m->attempt_count, 0);
 
     nv_printf(NV_DBG_ERRORS,
-        "AORUS Lever M-recover: resume — success_count=%d, attempt_count "
-        "reset to 0; emitting READY\n",
+        "AORUS Lever M-recover: resume — success_count=%d, bus reset done; "
+        "emitting READY (attempt_count cleared at next post-rmInit-OK)\n",
         atomic_read(&nvl->lever_m->success_count));
 
     tb_egpu_lever_m_emit_uevent(pdev, "READY");
 }
 EXPORT_SYMBOL(tb_egpu_lever_m_slot_reset_resume);
 
+/* Patch 0028 (2026-05-08): post-rmInit-OK hook.
+ *
+ * Called from nv.c after rm_init_adapter returns success — i.e. after
+ * GSP firmware has booted and the adapter is ready for use. This is
+ * the moment we can declare an end-to-end successful recovery (or a
+ * normal cold-boot init). Resets attempt_count to 0 so the next burst
+ * starts fresh.
+ *
+ * Safe to call on every cold-boot too (attempt_count is already 0 in
+ * the no-recovery-needed case, so this is idempotent). When the call
+ * follows a Lever M-recover bus reset cycle, this is what makes the
+ * H1 MaxAttempts gate meaningful: only verified-end-to-end recoveries
+ * clear the counter; failed retries accumulate and eventually surrender.
+ */
+void tb_egpu_lever_m_record_post_rminit_ok(nv_linux_state_t *nvl)
+{
+    int prev;
+
+    if (!nvl || !nvl->lever_m)
+        return;
+
+    prev = atomic_read(&nvl->lever_m->attempt_count);
+    if (prev > 0) {
+        nv_printf(NV_DBG_ERRORS,
+            "AORUS Lever M-recover: post-rmInit-OK observed with attempt_count=%d; "
+            "verified end-to-end recovery — resetting attempt_count to 0\n",
+            prev);
+    }
+    atomic_set(&nvl->lever_m->attempt_count, 0);
+}
+EXPORT_SYMBOL(tb_egpu_lever_m_record_post_rminit_ok);
+
 int tb_egpu_lever_m_recover_init(nv_linux_state_t *nvl)
 {
     struct tb_egpu_lever_m_recover *lm;
--- a/kernel-open/nvidia/nv.c
+++ b/kernel-open/nvidia/nv.c
@@ -1559,6 +1559,11 @@
     }
     /* AORUS Lever M-recover diagnostic: post-rmInit SUCCESS path. */
     tb_egpu_lever_m_diag_dump(nvl, "post-rmInit-OK");
+    /* AORUS Lever M-recover Patch 0028 (2026-05-08): verified end-to-end
+     * recovery — reset attempt_count so the H1 MaxAttempts gate measures
+     * consecutive *failed* full-recoveries, not raw retry count. Safe on
+     * cold boot (attempt_count=0 already; idempotent). */
+    tb_egpu_lever_m_record_post_rminit_ok(nvl);
 
     /* Generate and cache the UUID for future callers */
     (void)rm_get_gpu_uuid_raw(sp, nv);
